restrict timestamp to requested time range (cuts first entry and adds dummy last entry)\n\nThe following return types are supported\n: 'pandas'\n\n  : pandas DataFrame\n\n  'raw'\n\n  : tuple (header, values, secs, nanos)\n\nThe following time formats are supported:\n: 'raw'\n\n  : seconds (since beginning of year), nanoseconds\n\n  'timestamp'\n\n  : seconds since 01.01.1970 (default)\n\n  'datetime'\n\n  : datetime object ('pandas' only)\n\nReturns:\n\n: tuple of numpy arrays or pandas.DataFrame\n\nExample:\n\n```\nwith open('data.pb','rb') as f:\n    header, values, seconds, nanos = get_data(f.read(), return_type='raw')\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators", "bases": ["enum.Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.firstSample", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.lastSample", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.firstFill", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.lastFill", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.mean", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.min", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.max", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.count", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.ncount", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.nth", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.median", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bact_archiver.carchiver.ApplianceOperators.std"